The paper deals with the construction of models for process theories, which are relevant to several areas of computer science such as quantum computation, natural language processing, and network theory. The paper presents a parameterized framework for constructing these models, which involves generalizing the notion of binary relation along four axes of variation. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
